---

{# ── SUMMARY · real H2 carrying the consulting summary prose (right after the in-brief). (H2: The short version.) ── #}
<section class="section section--compact" id="ny-ind-consulting-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <h2 class="section__heading">The short version.</h2>
    </header>
    <p class="prose">{{ summarized | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── AI SUMMARY · five-question block. (H2: New York consulting accounting, in five questions.) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-ind-consulting-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">New York consulting accounting, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <dl class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled" id="ny-ind-consulting-ai-summary-list">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <dt class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</dt>
        <dd class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></dd>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </dl>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── CHALLENGES · three places the numbers slip (stack-8 cards in grid-3). (H2: Three places New York consultancies lose the real numbers. + 3 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-ind-consulting-challenges">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Why NY consulting books mislead</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Three places New York consultancies lose the real numbers.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">A busy, profitable-looking firm can still be subsidizing its worst clients. Knowing which of these you&rsquo;re in tells us where to start.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for c in challenges %}
      <article class="stack-8">
        <p class="section__eyebrow">{{ c.signal | safe }}</p>
        <h3>{{ c.heading | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ c.problem | safe }}</p>
        <p class="prose">{{ c.fix | safe }}</p>
        <p class="prose"><small>{{ c.honesty | safe }}</small></p>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── WHAT'S INCLUDED · grid-3 buyer-cards (6 services). (H2: New York consulting accounting, done by an expert. + 6 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-ind-consulting-included">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What TechBrot handles</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">New York consulting accounting, done by an expert.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Every engagement is scoped to your clients and service lines, delivered in your own QuickBooks file by a named Certified ProAdvisor.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for s in included %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ s.num }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ s.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="{{ s.href }}">{{ s.cta | safe }}</a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── TOOLS · integrations as checks-list (cobalt vocab; no integration-grid). (H2: Connected to how you run the practice.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-ind-consulting-tools">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Tools we work alongside</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Connected to how you run the practice.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">We reconcile what your time-tracking, PSA, billing, and payroll tools export into QuickBooks &mdash; you keep the stack you already run.</p>
    </header>
    <ul class="checks-list">
      {%- for t in tools %}
      <li>{{ t | safe }}</li>
      {%- endfor %}
    </ul>
    <p class="prose"><small>{{ toolsNote | safe }}</small></p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── PROCESS · four-phase cadence as stack-8 (cobalt vocab). (H2: From flat P&L to client-level profit. + 4 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-ind-consulting-process">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How engagements work</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">From flat P&amp;L to client-level profit.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Every New York consulting engagement follows the same four-phase rhythm &mdash; books accurate first, profit visibility second, advisory third.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for p in process %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="section__eyebrow">{{ p.phase }}</p>
        <h3>{{ p.heading | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ p.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <div class="hero__actions">
      <a class="btn btn--primary btn--lg" href="/contact/?intent=new-york&amp;state=new-york&amp;source_type=industry&amp;funnel_stage=MOFU">Book the discovery call</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── ADVISORY · standing brand line lives inside the body. (H2: Accurate client margins are the start. Pricing the work is the point.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-ind-consulting-advisory">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Beyond the books</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Accurate client margins are the start. Pricing the work is the point.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="stack-8">
      {%- for p in advisoryBody %}<p class="prose">{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── FAQ · 8 verbatim Q/A; visible faq__list = FAQPage schema (same array). (H2: New York consulting accounting questions.) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-ind-consulting-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Common questions</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">New York consulting accounting questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="ny-ind-consulting-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="ny-ind-consulting-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── EXPERT REVIEW · firm-level, no personal name (byline-block + trust-row + meta-reviewed). (H2: Reviewed by the TechBrot Certified ProAdvisor team.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-ind-consulting-review">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Page review &amp; standards</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Reviewed by the TechBrot Certified ProAdvisor team.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="byline-block">
      <div class="byline-block__mark" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div>
        <p class="byline-block__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p>
        <p class="byline-block__review">TechBrot Inc. &middot; Independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Reviewed and maintained by the accounting team at <strong>TechBrot Inc.</strong>, an independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm serving New York consulting and professional-services businesses remotely. Pricing reflects TechBrot&rsquo;s New York engagement ranges; New York sales-tax, NYC UBT, and multi-state nexus references reflect rules current as of the date below and are reviewed periodically against the <a href="https://www.tax.ny.gov/" rel="noopener nofollow">NY Department of Taxation &amp; Finance</a> and the <a href="https://www.nyc.gov/site/finance/index.page" rel="noopener nofollow">NYC Department of Finance</a>. TechBrot provides bookkeeping and coordinates with your CPA, who files and confirms taxability; we do not file NY State or NYC returns and do not determine your nexus position.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for c in reviewCreds %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ c.label }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ c.detail | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-14</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-14</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-14 &middot; Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── RELATED · grid-2 buyer-cards into NY services/industries. (H2: Related New York services & industries. + 4 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-ind-consulting-related">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Related</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Related New York services &amp; industries.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for r in related %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading"><a href="{{ r.href }}">{{ r.title | safe }}</a></h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ r.body | safe }}</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="{{ r.href }}">{{ r.cta | safe }}</a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
